When releasing a Maven project with the {{mvn release:prepare}} command, the related commits are ignored by Bamboo.
This is OK for the first commit (starting with "[maven-release-plugin] prepare release"), but the second commit should not be ignored ("[maven-release-plugin] prepare for next development iteration").

The exclusion pattern is hard-coded as:
{noformat}
\\[maven-release-plugin\\].*
{noformat}

The following pattern would be more appropriate:
{noformat}
\\[maven-release-plugin\\] prepare release.*
{noformat}

Bamboo doesn't let me to add notification to IM address in format of "user@server" as it notifies:
{quote}
Instant messaging address "tommi@im-server" is not in a valid format
{quote}

Still I'm able to test IM server configuration by sending test message to that address succesfully. Would be nice to disable that validation as user still can enter IM address to their profile in that format.

https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/BAMBOO/Git

The ":" is a port separator, 

{code}
[user@]host.xz:path/to/repo.git
{code}

should be
{code}
[user@]host.xz[:port]/path/to/repo.git
{code}

By default Bamboo has this this in the BAMBOO_INSTALL/webapp/WEB-INF/classes/log4j.properties:
{code}
log4j.category.com.atlassian.bamboo.filter.AccessLogFilter=DEBUG
{code}

Ship Bamboo with this parameter set to INFO to reduce the amount of logging.

I have a global variable:
{noformat}
job.config=my_job_config
{noformat}

And I have a plan variable:
{noformat}
maven.settings=${bamboo.job.config}/maven/myFile.xml
{noformat}

I've configured my plan to echo the {{maven.settings}} variable this way:
{noformat}
echo ${bamboo.maven.settings}
{noformat}

But when the plan is run I end up with:
{noformat}
Substituting variable: ${bamboo.maven.settings} with ${bamboo.job.config}/maven/myFile.xml
{noformat}

As can be seen, it *did not* resolve the nested variable to {{my_job_config}}.

I've realized that there's a paid third party plugin called [Bamboo Nested Variables|https://marketplace.atlassian.com/plugins/net.collabsoft.plugins.bamboo.nestedVariables] available in our Marketplace. However, if we suggest our customers to use this plugin and they have problems with it in the future, we probably won't be able to help them as much as we would like.

I have tried this behaviour on two URL's

{code}
1. deleting a label from a build using http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/result/{projectKey}-{buildKey}-{buildNumber}/label/{labelName}

2. Removing a build from the queue using http://myhost.com:8085/bamboo/rest/api/latest/queue/{projectKey}-{buildKey}-{buildNumber}
{code}
This is as per our REST API doco in the following links:

* https://developer.atlassian.com/static/rest/bamboo/3.3-SNAPSHOT.html
* https://developer.atlassian.com/display/BAMBOODEV/Bamboo+REST+Resources#BambooRESTResources-BuildQueueService
